VBScript showing hello world in client.

<html>
<body>
<script type="text/vbscript">
document.write("this is my first vbscript")
</script>
</bod>
</html>

IE->F12->document mode IE5-> 
now we can see the output of the code we wrote!

So, As I wrote here:
this is my first vbscript.

So this is my second vbscript:

<html>
<body>
<script type="text/vbscript">
Dim a
a = "ni hao ma"
b = 123
i = 1
alert(a & b)
Do while(i < 10)
document.write(i)
document.write("</br>")
i = i + 1
Loop
document.write("---------------------")
document.write("</br>")
Dim b
b = 10

Do until(b = 1)
document.write(b)
document.write("</br>")
b = b - 1
Loop

document.write(a)
document.write("this is an actionscript!")
</script>
</body>
</html>

After rendered by browser, it is like this:
